UNITED'S MAIN LINE AIRWAY
The Central Mid-Continent Route Linking the East
with All Pacific Coast Cities
UNITED AIR LINES
CONNECTING AIR LINES
FLYING UNITED'S MAIN LINE AIRWAY
In
amazingly swift time, your airplane carries you
comfortably and dependably across United's Main Line
airway - the NEW Overland Trail.
Your plane is the most modern. It has been minutely
inspected and thoroughly serviced before being dispatched
on this flight to insure that it is in first class mechanical
condition. It is manned by a skilled and competent crew
whose first consideration is your security and comfort. It
is completely equipped with plane ground radio facilities
and all other modern aids to precision air navigation. And
"behind the scenes" are hundreds of expert technicians-
dispatchers, mechanics, inspectors, radio operators, mete-
orologists and other air craftsmen— who contribute to the
clock-like operation of your schedule.
Your flight crosses some of the most interesting his-
torical and
geographical features in the country. The
Overland Trail—which United's Main Line airway paral-
lels-is outstanding in romance and color. For over 100
years it has been the leading route of East-West travel.
To acquaint you with the interesting features of the
Main Line airway, United presents you with this "Gay
Geography." The cartography is the work of Ruth Taylor.
For certain of the historical data included in this log,
United is indebted to Frank J. Taylor.
YOU ARE INVITED TO KEEP THIS "GAY GEOGRAPHY" AS A SOUVENIR OF YOUR FLIGHT.
